Merge pull request #1 from outis/jrswizzle

---

There are two changes here. The first implements class method swizzling in a very simple manner (call your instance method swizzling method on the meta-class). The second adds new functionality: instance & class method aliasing. This is perhaps outside the scope of JRSwizzle, but not too far outside. At the very least, its closely related. At its best, it broadens the scope of JRSwizzle to method manipulation. Is aliasing an appropriate addition for JRSwizzle?
